Title: Curse of Brightwood
Description: Search the old farms in north Brightwood for evidence of what may have caused the land to become cursed. Talk to Herbalist Lau in the Brightwood Settlement when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: It has been for three hundred years, if not longer. The plague of soullessness on Aeternum is stronger here.\n\nThe Lost are a far greater threat here than any Corruption - they dominate these lands.
InProgressResponse: Be wary of the Lost wandering around among those old farms. They can be quite dangerous in numbers.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Oh, hi there! Are you the one the Head Cleric sent out to collect soil samples from the northern townships?\n\nAh, perfect. Thank you! I'm Herbalist Lau, and you are?

Title: Inquisitor's Legacy
Description: Destroy the feared Inquisitor Lucia and recover her tools. Talk to Justiciar Farrell in the Brightwood Settlement when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: That's a history lesson for you. Three hundred years ago, all Aeternum was facing a plague of soullessness. \n\nThe Lost rising in unprecedented numbers, and the worst of it here in Brightwood. Course, I was but a lass then.
InProgressResponse: Inquisitor Lucia's talent for purging the soulless made her particularly dangerous when she became Lost.\n\nI'd exercise extreme caution.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Look at this - the legendary Inquisitor Lucia is down and you've recovered the tools of her trade.\n\nThese implements will help us in our campaign, {playerName}. You've done well.

Title: Restoring the Light
Description: Search Ballard's Manor and Dromgoole for the books of Sacrist Johannes and the amulets worn by his followers. Talk to Justiciar Farrell in the Brightwood Settlement when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Several, in fact. Head Cleric Pennyfather has been hesitant to go in search of them, but we know they're there.\n\nYou saw the old Cathedral, yes? The Inquisition - those were the glory years of Brightwood, to be sure.
InProgressResponse: The church in Brackwater is called Ballard's Curse now. You'll find the Sacrist's books there, and the soulless Lost who once followed him in the town nearby.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Aha! The Sacrist's books and those azoth-infused amulets.\n\nI must study Johannes's writing, but I believe with these, we'll be capable of battling the Lost like we haven't in three centuries!

Title: Lost and Returned
Description: Collect burial tokens from the Lost in various towns in Brightwood. Talk to Head Cleric Pennyfather in the Brightwood Settlement when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Same as it does everywhere else - something from the past becomes a plague to the present.\n\nThe Inquisition from three hundred years ago - we still don't know what happened.
InProgressResponse: I know it's gross, but I suspect we'll learn something. \n\nBring the burial tokens from the Lost to Head Cleric Pennyfather.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: It's good to see you again. Let's see, I'm forgetting your name at the moment…\n\nBut what's this? Burial tokens? From all those places? Oh, no…

Title: Held Below The Surface
Description: Confront Inquisitor Matthias, now among the Lost outside Brackwater, and bring his Medallion and Soul Candles to Justiciar Farrell in the Brightwood Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I'm starting to agree. At the very least, this means Justiciar Farrell's obsession with the Inquisition's tactics is ill-advised.\n\nOf course, she seems to have little respect for me these days.
InProgressResponse: Be wary if you go near Brackwater.\n\nIf Brightwood is cursed and Inquisitor Matthias responsible, it will be dangerous there.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: This medallion... it belonged to Inquisitor Matthias? Aye, this is another of the relics I've been seeking.\n\nOh, but it feels heavy, dark, laden with... suffering.

Title: Secrets of the Earth
Description: Defeat Bronzeroot warriors and search for the source of their ability to fight against the Lost. Talk to Embalmer Bankole in the Brightwood Settlement when the task is complete.
PlayerPrompt: "We should feel sorry for the Lost?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Of course. I have been here longer than these others, long enough that no one listens to old Bankole any more.\n\nI know things, though. I might even know how to bring relief to the soulless ones.
InProgressResponse: The Bronzeroot Warriors are a new expression of the Angry Earth, but they know the old ways.\n\nDefeat them and learn how it is that they so easily defeat the Lost.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: These satchels... their scent... do you smell it?  Moss Spores.\n\nIt makes sense, does it not? That which withers with half-death is susceptible to the energy of fresh life.

Title: Earth will Provide
Description: Defeat Bronzeroot warriors and collect any mossy growths in the area. Talk to Justiciar Farrell in the Brightwood Settlement when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Ah, but there is even a greater service you can perform.\n\nI believe this why the Bronzeroot adorn themselves as they do. Collect the full-grown samples from the area, and bring those to the Justiciar.
InProgressResponse: I believe the secrets the Bronzeroot Warriors employ will aid us greatly in protecting ourselves against the Lost.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, what's this? Moss from the Bronzeroot, eh? This is what gives them protection against the Lost?\n\nPerhaps the azoth in the water? Perfect, we will incorporate this into our armors, as well. You have my thanks.

Title: The New Threat
Description: Visit Shervey's Lumber Mill and investigate any Corruption that has spread there. Talk to Justiciar Sobol in the Brightwood Settlement when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Not to speak of, though there have been a few sightings, and some suspicions about the lumber mill.\n\nJusticiar Farrell said you've been helping her… any chance you can also check on the people at the lumber mill?
InProgressResponse: If Corruption has spread to the lumber mill, just make sure it's not going any further.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Oh, thank the heavens you've returned. No sooner had you departed then we heard the reports.\n\nThe Corruption had already taken over the lumber mill, but let me see - did you manage to learn anything else?

Title: Dark Legacy
Description: Defeat the Ghouls in Sinanovic Farm to collect bones. Talk to Head Cleric Pennyfather in the Brightwood Settlement when the task is done.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: He said that while the Inquisition made matters worse in Brightwood, it was not the source of the curse.\n\nHe said that legacy goes back more than a thousand years.
InProgressResponse: Go to the Sinanovic Farm to the south and collect the ghouls' bones. I worry what further horrors we might discover.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: What did you find - let's see… oh dear, I think I'm going to be sick. You can see it too, can't you?\n\nThese ghouls' bones were broken and then reformed, perhaps dozens of times.

Title: Heart of Darkness (Elite)
Description: Destroy Archminister Havelock on Brightwood Isle and collect his writings. Talk to Head Cleric Pennyfather in the Brightwood Settlement when the task is done.
PlayerPrompt: "Why did people commit such atrocities here ?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Azoth. Don't you see? By grinding up the bones of the Lost and perhaps even others, they sowed the earth with azoth.\n\nIt helped their crops, but at what cost? Think of the suffering it caused - of course the land is cursed.
InProgressResponse: Brightwood Isle is a source of terrible darkness in the center of Lake Genevieve. \n\nGo there if you dare to face Archminister Havelock, but I fear for your safety.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Strange, the moment you did the deed, I sensed it. I think we all did, though some might not have realized it.\n\nBut I do believe Havelock's fall may have restored some long-lost light to these lands.

Title: Trouble in the Fen
Description: Speak to Constable Kemal in Weaver's Fen to hear about some of the troubles they're facing with the Lost.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: That's what I heard. There were a few refugees that passed through recently.\n\nThey said there was trouble with the Lost and some illness that people in the Fen are contracting, as well. Be safe if you head out that way.
InProgressResponse: Whatever's happening in Weaver's Fen, I hope it stays there.\n\nBrightwood has seen it's share of dark times. We deserve a break… one of these days.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Are you the one who's just arrived from Brightwood, then?\n\nYes, yes. I heard things have improved a little over there. Suppose that's a good thing.

Title: Reaper's Locus (Expedition)
Description: Defeat the Starstone Reaper and Collect the Reaper's Locus. Talk to Herbalist Lau in the Brightwood Settlement when the task is done.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: We are both high achievers, at the top of our respective fields, mine being science, yours being… battle.\n\nIn fact, I wonder if you might partner with me to acquire an item of great scientific value?
InProgressResponse: Before you go marching into the Shattered Obelisk, I'd suggest finding some friends.\n\nWho knows what you'll find there? I just need the Reaper's Locus.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Oh, it's about time. You're such a talent, I frankly expected you to return much sooner.\n\nBut don't get me wrong - I'm very grateful. I'll take the Locus, and you can have this.

Title: Belly of the Corrupted
Description: Sabotage the food supply chain for the Corrupted at Reida's Burrow. Talk to Ranger Shui Tijong in Brightwood when the task is done.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: My thoughts exactly - we can warn the settlement later.  We must strike hard and fast.\n\nI have been watching the Corrupted forces' movements since they arrived.
InProgressResponse: If we destroy the hunters and claim all their rations, the Corrupted forces' supply lines will be in dire straits.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Well done, friend. With their rations stolen and their hunters compromised, the Corrupted will be hungry.\n\nHungry soldiers are desparate soldiers and desparate soldiers are sloppy.

Title: Infernal Armaments
Description: Assault the Corrupted Forces' weapon-making operations at the Iron Fields. Talk to Ranger Shui Tijong in Brightwood when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: The main thrust of the Corrupted operations here is the mission to supply their forces with armaments.\n\nThey have a start-to-finish process under way, mining the ore and forging the weapons.
InProgressResponse: The Iron Fields is where the Corrupted forces' weaponmaking operations is most vulnerable.\n\nStrike there and they will not soon recover.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Did you manage to get the weapons? Excellent, excellent. Let me see...\n\nThese are… very well-made weapons for the Corrupted. How… oh no, it can't be! Master Smith McCoy?

Title: Blacksmith Betrayer
Description: Destroy Master Smith McCoy who's running Corlew's Mining Operations, and reclaim McCoy's Weapon Designs. Talk to Ranger Shui Tijong in Brightwood when the task is done.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: There can be no doubt - McCoy is the one leading this operation in Corlew's Mine.\n\nI fear with him in charge, our efforts will prove to have been only a minor setback for the Corrupted.
InProgressResponse: Though I worry about what resistance you'll meet fighting your way in, I have to admit, taking out Master Smith McCoy quickly does seem wise.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Is McCoy down then? Ah, and his designs? Excellent! This will disrupt the Corrupted's supply chain.\n\nI salute your courage, Warrior, and your valor. There are few who could do what you have done.

Title: Location Scout
Description: Search for vibrant waterfalls for Wolcott to paint and place an easel at each one. Talk to Painter Wolcott in Brightwood when the task is done.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Sadly, I don’t have time to both find all the beautiful locations and paint them. Searching cannot be rushed, and it takes me so long to get my paints arranged just how I like them. \n\nBut perhaps you could help!
InProgressResponse: I need some inspiration, something that jumps out of the landscape and onto a canvas! \n\nGo on, I'm counting on you to find it!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Marvelous! The rushing water, the way the sunlight glints through the trees. Yes, yes! I can work with this.

Title: Eye for Reflection
Description: Search for dynamic waterfalls for Wolcott to paint and place an easel at each one. Talk to Painter Wolcott in Brightwood when the task is done.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: How dynamic it makes an image. How alive you feel when seeing it. How it moves, even when still. \n\nI can already tell these waterfalls will be best sellers. I’m going to need more locations!
InProgressResponse: You were such help before that I need your help again. \n\nSearch for energetic waterfalls I can use as reference.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: These are magnificent! Thank you for marking their locations on my map. I can only hope my waterfall paintings are able to compete with what is already out there.

Title: Wolcott's Masterpiece
Description: Search for picturesque lakes for Wolcott to paint and place an easel at each one. Talk to Painter Wolcott in Brightwood when the task is done.
PlayerPrompt: "There are some nice lakes around here."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I’ve decided that my next collection of paintings will be of the local lakes. \n\nSomething restful to the eye, and calming to the soul. They are certain to be popular!
InProgressResponse: The waterfalls you found before were just lovely. \n\nNow I need three lakes for my next paintings!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Superb! The locations you have chosen fit perfectly within the landscape, like a slice of sky fallen to the ground. \n\nPainting these lakes will be a joy. And Cole hasn’t painted anything like them yet!

Title: A Simple Tea
Description: Fight the Bronzeroot Dryads of the Green Defile for the Undefiled Tea Leaves and bring them back to Naturalist Khunbish in Brightwood.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: The soullessness of the Lost has ravaged Brightwood for centuries. Some say the land is cursed.\n\nBut the Angry Earth thrive down there, despite all the death around them.
InProgressResponse: The Bronzeroot of the Green Defile carry these special tea leaves.\n\nCollect some for me, and I will reward you.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, do you have them, then? Yes, these leaves are perfect!\n\nThe tea I can brew from these leaves, well, I am not even sure of all of its properties.

Title: Sweet Secrets
Description: Find Lush Sugarsap from the Trees in Lush Hideaway and bring them back to Naturalist Khunbish in Brightwood so that she can drink the tea she's brewing.
PlayerPrompt: "A little honey should do the trick."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: No, I have sworn not to partake in the sweet product of the Apoidea.\n\nThe trees from the south caverns will yield Lush Sugarsap, but the Angry Earth there are very protective.
InProgressResponse: It is not the Wyrdwood trees I speak of but the regular trees in the cavern that will yield the Lush Sugarsap.\n\nThank you for your help.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: There! Please tell me you were able to get the Lush Sugarsap! Yes, this will do!\n\nNow, at least I will be able to drink this tea, assuming I have what I need to brew it.

Title: Verdant Adelphia
Description: Collect Adelphian Tubers from the Verdant Cavern and bring them to Naturalist Khunbish in Brightwood so she can finally make her tea.
PlayerPrompt: "Let me guess - you need something else?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I do, though I fear I have imposed on you enough, traveler. \n\nIf the Angry Earth weren't so cruel, I would not be in such a position. They hoard their secrets even from their allies.
InProgressResponse: None of this would be necessary if they would just allow me back into the fold. This tea, and those Adelphian Tubers, are now the only way.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Did you defeat the Shamans? Aha! The tubers! This is the last ingredient!\n\nNow, I can finally brew the magical tea which will redeem me to the Angry Earth.

Title: Azoth Tree Achene (Elite)
Description: Defeat the Angry Earth Leader Ceran at the Azoth Tree and collect his Achene. Talk to Naturalist Khunbish in Brightwood when the task is done.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: It was the leader of the Angry Earth in this region who cast me out - a Dryad Archer named Ceran.\n\nEven with the tea you have give me, he might just cast me out again.
InProgressResponse: Destroy Ceran and bring me his Achene, and then, I will be able to walk among the Angry Earth again.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ceran is gone. I can sense it. You have done well, more than you know - you have restored the true order here.\n\nI am sorry I could not tell you the whole truth before.

Title: Bear Co-Habitation
Description: Help Hunter Hutchison in Brightwood get vengeance against some savage bears in Greyvale that destroyed his family.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: No. They don't want me. They've made that painfully clear.\n\nMy wife Susan and I lived among them for decades, in perfect harmony. Until a few months ago.
InProgressResponse: I still can't get over it. Out of nowhere, they just turned on us.\n\nHelp me get my vengeance, and I'll be in your debt.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: I heard those bastards snarling and growling all the way down here.\n\nWhy we're only giving them what they deserve.

Title: Papa Bear (Elite)
Description: Hunter Hutchison has asked you to destroy Gren, the massive bear who killed his wife, and reclaim his wife's ring. Bring the ring back to Hunter Hutchinson in Brightwood.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Nah, Susan and these bears are the only real family I ever had.\n\nLiving out there, foraging for honey, hibernating… it's the only life I know, the only place I feel at home.
InProgressResponse: It was that monster Gren that ate my sweet wife.\n\nDestroy him, and then I can return to the family, those I have left.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: It's done then? That monstrosity of a bear gone? You're a brave soul, and a hardy one too.\n\nAll right, I'll work up the nerve and go back home. If they turn on me again, I don't know. Guess I'll end up like Susan.

Title: Memories of Another Life
Description: Megara Pantazis lived in the Walsham area many decades ago. She's asked you to retrieve her mementos from the town and return them to her in Brightwood so she can relive her past.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: The town of Walsham fell to the Lost… it's been more years than I can count.\n\nBelieve it or not, the wedding was on this very spot -  a moment I never want to forget. He was the love of my life.
InProgressResponse: Those years in Walsham were the best I had.\n\nIf you could recover those Mementos, it would mean a lot.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Well, look at these! You found all my old mementos.\n\nIt's sad, isn’t it? Or it should be. But for some reason, it's only reminding me of all the good times we had.

Title: Home No More
Description: Megara Pantazis has decided she wants to join the love of her life as a Lost. She's asked you to find her journal in Marcel's Hamlet and bring it to her in Brightwood so that she might read it and despair.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: What I'm saying is that I've spent all these years trying to keep my chin up, rallying for life.\n\nMeanwhile, the love of my life is Lost, and soon, even forgotten. I've decided I want to join him.
InProgressResponse: I kept the journal for years and years, when our love was forbidden, and then after.\n\nThe journal will get me there - I feel certain.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Is that it? Oh good gods, look at that old thing. Tattered and weathered, but still in one piece.\n\nLet me read it, this should bring back all that despair I felt then. This is the way I'll rejoin my love.

Title: Til Death do us Part (Elite)
Description: Megara Pantazis has admitted the love of her life was actually Pastor Walsham. She's asked you be sure nothing of his human nature remains before she joins him as a Lost. Talk to her in Brightwood when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: The truth about my true love. I didn't tell you the whole story.\n\nThe wedding that took place here, it wasn't where I married my true love, it's where I met him.
InProgressResponse: My love was a formidable man in life. I suspect he will be difficult to defeat. Do take care.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Tell me, did you see him? Did he seem miserable as a Lost, or actually at peace? What did you find? \n\nWhat is this?

Title: Dispatches from the North
Description: Innkeep Okorie in Brightwood says the settlement has received no dispatches from Great Cleave. They've asked you to search for missing dispatches in Cleave's Malice and take them to Eastburn Outpost and let them know they were never delivered.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Mm. That's the cause for my concern. Ingram Kent, the Innkeep at Eastburn, was sending regular dispatches until the last few weeks.\n\nI fear the dispatches are being intercepted by the Corrupted forces entrenched at Cleaves' Malice.
InProgressResponse: I should think at least one of the dispatches from Eastburn would have made it through.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: A brave soul indeed to venture this far behind enemy lines. Eastburn is a small ship on a sea of evil.\n\nWhat's this, though? The dispatches I sent to Brightwood… undelivered? Where did you find them?

Title: Battle's Embrace
Description: Recover the patterns and components needed to craft the Battle's Embrace Armor. Talk to Justiciar Sobol in Brightwood when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: True, true. But I've heard of something that could help against the troubles.\n\nLegendary armor that makes the wearer into a veritable fortress!
InProgressResponse: Keep alert for any of the materials needed to craft Battle's Embrace.\n\nWearing that armor is sure to inspire an entire generation of new warriors to fight against the Corrupted.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Do my eyes deceive me? You found all the materials to craft Battle's Embrace?\n\nYes, yes! To think, I get to see this legendary armor in action!

Title: Best Foot Forward
Description: Collect Stout Fenton Hides from Fenton Hamlet, Treated Hobnails from Cayo de la Muerte, and Restless Metal Bands from Festering Flotsam. Then visit a Tier 3 Forge to craft the Battle's Embrace Boots.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: @0205_0102_01_Boots_proposal
InProgressResponse: @0205_0102_01_Boots_incomplete
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: @0205_0102_01_Boots_complete

Title: Embrace the Fight
Description: Collect Stalwart Rivets from The Golden Princess, Evershine Polish from Gelida Pillars, and Hammered Metal from Acedia Bastion. Then visit a Tier 3 Forge to craft the Battle's Embrace Breastplate.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: @0205_0102_02_Breastplate_proposal
InProgressResponse: @0205_0102_02_Breastplate_incomplete
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: @0205_0102_02_Breastplate_complete

Title: Grievous Blows
Description: Collect Baneseed Oil from Fort Damnation, Attuned Starmetal from Propus, and Reforged Plating from Olympus. Then visit a Tier 3 Forge to craft the Battle's Embrace Greaves.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: @0205_0102_03_Greaves_proposal
InProgressResponse: @0205_0102_03_Greaves_incomplete
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: @0205_0102_03_Greaves_complete

Title: Running the Gauntlet
Description: Collect Refined Balefire from Svikin's Stand, Flexible Mesh from Vela, and Essence of Power from Litheltop. Then visit a Tier 3 Forge to craft the Battle's Embrace Gauntlets.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: @0205_0102_04_Gauntlets_proposal
InProgressResponse: @0205_0102_04_Gauntlets_incomplete
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: @0205_0102_04_Gauntlets_complete

Title: Ahead of the Rest
Description: Collect Rugged Varnish from Nettlevex, Shards of Battle from Lower Slag Mine, and Heavy Padding from Upper Slag Mine. Then visit a Tier 3 Forge to craft the Battle's Embrace Helm.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: @0205_0102_05_Helm_proposal

Title: Marauder Advancement: Gladiator
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Gladiator and then complete the Trial of the Gladiator Quest from the Faction Representative in Cutlass Keys.

Title: Marauder Advancement: Gladiator
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Gladiator and then complete the Trial of the Gladiator Quest from the Faction Representative in Cutlass Keys.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I knew I saw that spark of ambition. You are Marauder through and through, Soldier.\n\nYou seek to become a Gladiator then? Complete missions to earn reputation, then you can face the Trial of the Gladiator in Cutlass Keys.
InProgressResponse: Now that you have officially joined our ranks, we expect you to seize every opportunity to gain honor.\n\nMissions are available anytime on the Faction Board here, and in other settlements.

Title: Marauder Advancement: Gladiator
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Gladiator and then complete the Trial of the Gladiator Quest from the Faction Representative in Cutlass Keys.

Title: Marauder Advancement: Gladiator
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Gladiator and then complete the Trial of the Gladiator Quest from the Faction Representative in Cutlass Keys.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I knew I saw that spark of ambition. You are Marauder through and through, Soldier.\n\nYou seek to become a Gladiator then? Complete missions to earn reputation, then you can face the Trial of the Gladiator in Cutlass Keys.
InProgressResponse: We are strongest together. Let us endeavor to bring victory to the Marauders.

Title: Marauder: Trial of the Gladiator
Description: Defeat the Lost Pirate Hamidou to prove you're worthy to advance to the rank of Gladiator. Talk to Ravager Silas in Cutlass Keys when the task is complete.
PlayerPrompt: "Can't be too hard. You made it."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Oh, a really smart tongue on this one. It's a shame I don't have time to make you back it up.\n\nThis challenge will be too much anyhow, I'd bet my career you'll fail.
InProgressResponse: Smart. You should put off facing Hamidou for as long as possible.\n\nMaybe even forever.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You defeated Hamidou? You? You… weasel. Just cost me a pile of azoth on that bet.\n\nVery well, you're a Gladiator. Now, get on your way before I smash your face.

Title: Marauder Advancement: Ravager
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Ravager and then complete the Trial of the Ravager Quest from the Faction Representative in Weaver's Fen.

Title: Marauder: Trial of the Ravager
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\nDefeat enemies across Weaver's Fen to advance to the rank of Ravager. Talk to Commander Bergeron in Weaver's Fen when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Be wary of what you wish for, young warrior. This test will have you wading through swampwater, and through blood.\n\nTravel the Fen and face the enemies it throws at you. I will await you here.
InProgressResponse: Face whatever challenges the Fen sends your way, and then you will be a Ravager.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, the victor returns. Success in battle feeds the soul like nothing else, does it not?\n\nI welcome you to the ranks of the Ravagers, {playerName}. Though I fear Ravager Silas will not be pleased.

Title: Marauder Advancement: Destroyer
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Destroyer and then complete the Trial of the Destroyer Quest from the Faction Representative in Restless Shore.

Title: Marauder: Trial of the Destroyer
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\nDestroy enemies from each region of Mourningdale to prove you're worthy to advance to the rank of Destroyer. Talk to Destroyer Garcia in Restless Shores when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Because you apparently committed some offense against Ravager Silas. She does not take things lightly.\n\nBut come, are you prepared to face the trial to advance your rank?
InProgressResponse: I have great faith in you, my friend. Face the enemies you must, and prove yourself an ultimate warrior.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Aha! Victory! You join the upper ranks of the Marauders now, {playerName}.\n\nIt is an esteemed position. And you have exceeded Ravager Silas's rank. She will be furious.

Title: Marauder Advancement: Commander
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Commander and then complete the Trial of the Commander Quest from the Faction Representative in Ebonscale Reach.

Title: Marauder: Trial of the Commander
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\nDefeat Corrupted Ravager Silas to prove you're worthy to advance to the rank of Commander. Talk to Commander Hartford in Ebonscale when the task is complete.
PlayerPrompt: "I am ready. What do I do?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Unfortunately, your trial is going to have to be rather unique.\n\nAs you may recall, Ravager Silas developed quite a rivalry with you. Her rage drove her to become Corrupted.
InProgressResponse: There is a sad irony to the way this thing has unfolded.\n\nRavager Silas must be destroyed.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: I know that can't have been pleasant. We must honor the memory of what Silas aspired to, rather than what she became.\n\nOn a much brighter note, I am proud to bestow on you the title of 'Commander'.

Title: Syndicate Advancement: Scrivener
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Scrivener and then complete the Trial of the Scrivener Quest from the Faction Representative in Brightwood.

Title: Syndicate Advancement: Scrivener
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Scrivener and then complete the Trial of the Scrivener Quest from the Faction Representative in Brightwood.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: There are no shortcuts in the Syndicate; it will take time and considerable effort to advance. \n\nTo become a Scrivener, you will complete missions to earn reputation, then you can face the Trial of the Scrivener in Brightwood.
InProgressResponse: Now that you have officially joined in our enterprise, you should always seek ways to advance our interests.\n\nMissions are available anytime on the Faction Board here, and in other settlements.

Title: Syndicate Advancement: Scrivener
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Scrivener and then complete the Trial of the Scrivener Quest from the Faction Representative in Brightwood.

Title: Syndicate Advancement: Scrivener
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Scrivener and then complete the Trial of the Scrivener Quest from the Faction Representative in Brightwood.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: There are no shortcuts in the Syndicate; it will take time and considerable effort to advance. \n\nTo become a Scrivener, you will complete missions to earn reputation, then you can face the Trial of the Scrivener in Brightwood.
InProgressResponse: I humbly greet you, truth seeker.

Title: Syndicate: Trial of the Scrivener
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\nDefeat Lost Gheist Malikor and use the Psychokinetic Absorber to capture any soul remnants to earn the rank of Scrivener. Talk to Scrivener Krockes in Brightwood when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: You have arrived at the perfect moment, for I am ready to test my new Psychokinetic Absorber.\n\nDid you know that some of the Lost still have traces of their souls?
InProgressResponse: Have you found Malikor yet? He's somewhere out there.\n\nUse the Absorber and bring back the traces of his soul!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, at last! Yes, yes, you see? There are traces of Malikor's soul in here! This changes EVERYTHING!\n\nYou have done well, and I am pleased to promote you to Scrivener! Yes, yes. Now I must work!

Title: Syndicate Advancement: Chronicler
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Chronicler and then complete the Trial of the Chronicler Quest from the Faction Representative in Weaver's Fen.

Title: Syndicate: Trial of the Chronicler
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\nGather specimens from the various Lost in Weaver's Fen and return to Alchemist Rubis in Weaver's Fen to earn the rank of Chronicler.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Indeed. Alchemist Krockes had wanted to be here for this, but I see no reason to delay.\n\nGather me specimens from the various Lost here in the Fen, and I'll promote you to 'Chronicler'.
InProgressResponse: Gather the specimens for our work here in the Fen, and then I will see you advanced in rank.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Really? You got all the specimens? And rather quickly too, I think.\n\nPerhaps this will aid in my research to the same extent your previous work helped Krockes. That would be a boon.

Title: Syndicate Advancement: Cabalist
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Cabalist and then complete the Trial of the Cabalist Quest from the Faction Representative in Mourningdale.

Title: Syndicate: Trial of the Cabalist
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\nPlace Psychokinetic Absorbers at strategic points in Mourningdale to earn the rank of Cabalist. Talk to Cabalist Crawford in Mourningdale when the task is done.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: For you, we have arranged for an extension of your previous work with soul traces.\n\nYou have used a Psychokinetic Absorber before - you practically made them famous!
InProgressResponse: Those Psychokinetic Absorbers won't place themselves.\n\nThe sooner, the better. Mores collected that way.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Perfect! Perfect! You have accomplished quite a feat, and I suspect there will be quite a yield when Krockes arrives.\n\nYes, you deserve the title of Cabalist. You are an incredible asset to the Syndicate.

Title: Syndicate Advancement: Alchemist
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Alchemist and then complete the Trial of the Alchemist Quest from the Faction Representative in Reekwater.

Title: Syndicate: Trial of the Alchemist
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\nDefeat Alchemist Krockes and absorb his soul into the Psychokinetic Absorber and then take it to the Dryads in Reekwater to destroy it to earn the rank of Alchemist. Talk to Alchemist Santos in Reekwater when the task is done.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: The way it always does with the undisciplined, too enamored of her research and her reputation.\n\nKrockes was simply not strong-minded enough, unlike you. You are ready to face your final trial, are you not?
InProgressResponse: When you find Krockes, don't hesitate. I suspect he has become quite… volatile.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Then the deed is done? Krockes is no more. Well done!\n\nThe integrity of our research must be preserved. You have earned the disctinction and rank of Alchemist. Congratulations!

Title: Covenant Advancement: Templar
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Templar and then complete the Trial of the Templar Quest from the Faction Representative in Brightwood.

Title: Covenant Advancement: Templar
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Templar and then complete the Trial of the Templar Quest from the Faction Representative in Brightwood.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: It will take great heart and great courage should you wish to rise within the order.\n\nTo become a Templar, you'll need to complete missions to earn reputation, and then face the Trial of the Templar in Brightwood.
InProgressResponse: Now that you have joined in our cause, you must carry the light into the world at every chance.\n\nMissions are available anytime on the Faction Board here, and in other settlements.

Title: Covenant Advancement: Templar
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Templar and then complete the Trial of the Templar Quest from the Faction Representative in Brightwood.

Title: Covenant Advancement: Templar
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Templar and then complete the Trial of the Templar Quest from the Faction Representative in Brightwood.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: It will take great heart and great courage should you wish to rise within the order.\n\nTo become a Templar, you'll need to complete missions to earn reputation, and then face the Trial of the Templar in Brightwood.
InProgressResponse: The light of the Covenant shines within you.

Title: Covenant: Trial of the Templar
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\nTrack down the missing Covenant Initiate Bremen Luca and attempt to discover what happened to him to advance to the rank of Templar. Talk to Templar Roose in Brightwood when the task is complete.
PlayerPrompt: "I am ready. What do I do?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: One of our number - an Initiate like yourself - has become enamored of some… unorthodox ideas.\n\nHe has attracted a following, and they all must be brought back into the fold.
InProgressResponse: Find the Apostate and bring him back here.\n\nWe will purge these ideas from his mind, one way or another.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, you have bad news… unfortunately, this is the fate awaiting any of us who stray from the path.\n\nIt was a mercy that you put him down. Did you find anything else?

Title: Covenant Advancement: Excubitor
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Excubitor and then complete the Trial of the Excubitor Quest from the Faction Representative in Weaver's Fen.

Title: Covenant: Trial of the Excubitor
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\nPut to rest some of those who've fallen in Weaver's Fen to advance to the rank of Excubitor. Talk to Adjudicator Sheng in Weaver's Fen when the task is complete.
PlayerPrompt: "Only if it helps me be of greater service."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I have no doubt that it will. I sense that you are not meant to remain a Templar forever.\n\nI heard about that tragic business with the Apostate, Bremen Luca.
InProgressResponse: Travel the Fen and put down those who have fallen. That will earn you the rank of Excubitor.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: It's a somber business, the campaign we are engaged in here in the Fen.\n\nYou have done more than your part. Congratulations on your advancement, Excubitor {playerName}.

Title: Covenant Advancement: Lumen
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Lumen and then complete the Trial of the Lumen Quest from the Faction Representative in Great Cleave.

Title: Covenant: Trial of the Lumen
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\nRecover Prayer Beads from Corrupted Templars to earn the rank of Lumen. Talk to Excubitor Luca in Great Cleave when the task is done.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: It seems you do not recognize my name, but I am Livia Luca.\n\nThe alleged apostate you tracked down in Brightwood was my only son.
InProgressResponse: I am the one who gets to determine your trial.\n\nBring me the prayer beads if you wish to advance in rank.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Let's see what you found. Yes, you see? Covenant Prayer Beads on the Corrupted.\n\nHow many must fall before Adjudicator Maras is exposed? Spark be with us - this ends here!

Title: Covenant Advancement: Adjudicator
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION ADVANCEMENT QUEST</font>\nEarn enough Faction Reputation to qualify for the rank of Adjudicator and then complete the Trial of the Adjudicator Quest from the Faction Representative in Shattered Mountain.

Title: Covenant: Trial of the Adjudicator
Description: <font color="#eaeaea">FACTION TRIAL QUEST</font>\n Destroy the Corrupted Excubitor Luca to earn the rank of Adjudicator. Talk to Adjudicator Maras in Shattered Mountain when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Sometimes the darkest shadow lies within, my friend. Such was the case with Livia Luca.\n\nHer obsession with her son's legacy and her paranoia caused her to become Corrupted.
InProgressResponse: The light guides our path, and right now, for you, it shines on Excubitor Luca. \n\nShe must be destroyed.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Then it is done? Spark light her way into a more peaceful place.\n\nWe have purged the Corruption from our ranks. Congratulations, I am proud to pronounce you as an Adjudicator. You are one of us, now.

Title: Executioner
Description: Acquire Bucaneer's Plank from Stone Skull Fort, Hangman's Binding from Wayward Mounds, Blade of the Brutes from Plundering Shark, and the Infernal Coagulant from Grus to craft the infamous Axe, "Executioner." Talk to Head Cleric Pennyfather in the Brightwood Settlement when the task is complete.
PlayerPrompt: "I'd be interested in a legendary axe."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Ah, yes. I'm interested too… wait, what were we talking about? Oh yes - the Executioner.\n\nI'll give you a list of the elements required to reforge it. They might be a challenge to find, but I think it's worth it.
InProgressResponse: Oh! It's… your name is still eluding me, but I remember something about… oh yes, the axe, Executioner.\n\nGood luck finding everything you'll need.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Wait a minute… this is… you found everything needed to reforge Executioner?\n\nImpressive, very impressive. That is a very effective weapon if used… properly. Wield it well.

Title: Collect items used to craft the Executioner
Description: The most treacherous of pirates only know one love: the sea's embrace.

Title: Collect items used to craft the Executioner
Description: Those bound to their fates in a gallows cannot escape them. Only you can deliver them.

Title: Collect items used to craft the Executioner
Description: The most brutal of us must give away their mercy, for they have none to show their foes.

Title: Collect items then craft the Executioner
Description: Even the hottest blood running through veins oft still into fetid darkness.

Title: Hope Manifest
Description: Acquire Mender's Cloth from Seele's Stake, Soothsayer's Salve from Catara Falls, Mercy's Breath from Eridanus, and the Hope Catalyst from Vela to craft the legendary Life Staff, "Hope Manifest." Talk to Embalmer Bankole in Brightwood when the task is complete.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Oh, you would not find such a thing, not for many centuries now. But I can show you to remake it.\n\nTake this list of the elements required, and then you can make the staff, "Hope Manifest."
InProgressResponse: You seek the elements of the staff, still?\n\nYou will find them, if you keep trying.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: There is the new light of Brightwood, and you found everything you needed, yes?\n\nWith that staff in hand, you are the very thing, "Hope Manifest." Brightness will follow, wherever you go.

Title: Collect items used to craft Hope Manifest
Description: Healing lies in the cloth of the mender, who dresses wounds carefully like an aegis.

Title: Collect items used to craft Hope Manifest
Description: Healing lies in the salve of the sooth sayer, a calming touch to numb pain.

Title: Collect items used to craft Hope Manifest
Description: Healing lies in the Breath of Mercy, a gift from the Fates who continue to weave.

Title: Collect items then craft Hope Manifest
Description: Healing lies in hope, the hope to live, and those who catalyze that hope.
